                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="a2">
                           <locus target="#99vb">Fols. 99vb-100</locus>r: Donation note.<q xml:lang="gez">Fol. 99vb-100r: ዝመጽሐፍ፡ ዘወይዘሮ፡ ካህሳ፡ ስመ፡ አቡሃ፡ በረከተ፡ አብ፡ ስመ፡ እማ፡ ወለተ፡ መድኅን፡ ወእሁሃ፡ መንግሥተ፡ አብ፡ ዘወሀበቶ፡ ታቦተ፡ ሚካኤል፡ [fol.10ra] ቀርን፡ ሰበር፡ ከመ፡ ይኩን፡ መርሃ፡ ለመንግሥተ፡ ሰማያት፡ ዘሰረቆ፡ ወዘፈሐቆ፡ ውጉዝ፡ ይኩን፡ በአፈ፡ ጴጥሮስ። መምሬ፡ ተክለ፡ ሃይማኖት፡ ወዘአጽሐፎ፡ በእደ፡ አቡነ፡ ገበረ፡ እግዚአብሔር።</q>
                           <q xml:lang="en">Fols. 99vb-100r: This book is of wäyzäro Kahsa and the name of her father (is) Bäräkätä ʾAb, the name of her mother Wälättä Mädḫǝn and her brother Mängǝśtä ʾAb, which she donated to the tabot of Mikaʾel [fol. 10ra] of Qärn Säbär, so that it might be her guide to the Kingdom of Heavens; may be condemned by the mouth of Peter who stole it or erased it. MämreTäklä Haymanot caused the book to be written by the hand of ʾabunä Gäbrä ʾƎgziʾabǝḥer.</q>
                           The note mentions the donor wäyzäro Kahsa and members of her family. Also, it includes the name of the scribe ʾabunä Gäbrä ʾƎgziʾabǝḥer and mämre Täklä Haymanot, who commissioned the writing. Written in the same hand as the main text.
                        </item>
